\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1.1}{\ignorespaces A timed automaton \(\mathcal  {A}_1\). Both clocks \(x\) and \(y\) start at \(0\) in state \(q_0\). The transition on \(a\) from \(q_0\) to \(q_1\) has the guard \(x \leq 2\), forcing the system to spend at most \(2\) time units before taking it. The transition on \(a\) from \(q_1\) to \(q_0\) has no guard and resets \(x\). The guard on \(b\) from \(q_1\) to \(q_2\) requires that at least \(10\) time units have elapsed since the start, via the constraint \(y \geq 10\).\relax }}{7}{figure.caption.10}\protected@file@percent }
