\newlabel{fig:jump-decrement}{{3.7}{68}{Decrement gadget for counter $C_1$. The highlighted horizontal bars are the synchronizing nodes $n_1$ and $n_3$; the middle node $n_2$ is deliberately unsynchronizing. The gadget first copies the current reference time of $p_1$ into the witness agent $r_1$, then advances $p_1$ and $q_1$ together until $q_1$ catches up with that frozen witness. The branch taken afterwards depends on whether a positive amount of time was needed.\relax }{figure.caption.221}{}}
